      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Media Queries?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Media queries are used to apply CSS styles based on device characteristics like screen size, width, height, and orientation."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Syntax"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "@media (max-width: 768px) {\n  body {\n    background: lightblue;\n  }\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Breakpoints"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Device", "Width"],
        "rows": [
          ["Mobile", "≤ 768px"],
          ["Tablet", "769px – 1024px"],
          ["Desktop", "≥ 1025px"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Min vs Max Width"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "@media (min-width: 768px) {\n  /* styles for larger screens */\n}\n\n@media (max-width: 768px) {\n  /* styles for smaller screens */\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Mobile First Approach"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "/* Base styles for mobile */\nbody { font-size: 14px; }\n\n/* Larger screens */\n@media (min-width: 768px) {\n  body { font-size: 16px; }\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Multiple Conditions"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "@media (min-width: 600px) and (max-width: 1024px) {\n  body { background: yellow; }\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Orientation"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "@media (orientation: landscape) {\n  body { background: lightgreen; }\n}"
